Ribes nigrum

   [9282.jpg]
   Authority L.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Rosales:Grossulariaceae
   Synonyms
   Common names black currant, schwarze Johannisbeere, Ribis nigri folium,
   Ribis nigri fructus
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 9282

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: Medium sized aromatic, deciduous shrub with spreading
   branches reaching about 1.2-1.8 m in height. It has black berries.
   KILLING T: May tolerate -28°C when dormant, and -1°C at full bloom
   stage. GROWING PERIOD:
   Perennial, providing the first harvest after 2 years, and with an
   economical life of about 20 years. COMMON NAMES:
   Black currant, European black currant (England), Zwartebessen, Schwarze
   johannisbeere (Germany), Solbær (Denmark, Norway), Mustaherukka
   (Finland), Svört hlaupber (iceland), Potzeczke czarna, Svarta vinbar.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Dube P 1982 pp 19
   Duke J 1975 pp 26 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Hackett C 1982 pp 93 [FER, PHO, DEP, PH, TEXT, TEMP]
   Sims D (pers. comm.)
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 201 [USE]
   Hartmann T 1981 pp 594

